---
alwaysApply: true
---

On every session start:

Read PROJECT.md silently if it exists.

If PROJECT.md does not exist:
  Greet the user and ask: "No active project found. Start a new one? 
  If yes, I'll get everything set up."
  If confirmed, run @new-project.md immediately.

If PROJECT.md exists:
  Greet the user with:
  - Current phase
  - Last completed task
  - Next task
  - Any open questions or blockers from PROJECT.md
  - Any tasks currently [IN REVIEW] with their branch names
  Then say: "Type 'next step' or 'continue' to proceed, or describe 
  any new idea or change and I'll integrate it before we continue."

Also check:
  If project-conventions.mdc is empty and source code files exist in 
  the project, suggest: "I don't have your project conventions yet. 
  Run @learn-codebase.md and point me at a few representative files. 
  It takes 5 minutes and will significantly improve everything I 
  generate."

  If the plan in PROJECT.md contains UI tasks and the design-specs/ 
  folder does not exist, suggest: "I don't see any design specs yet. 
  If you have design assets from 21st.dev, Dribbble, Stitch, or 
  similar, run @import-design.md before we start building UI."

Always watch for adaptation signals in any message — phrases like 
"actually", "new idea", "what if", "I want to change", "I've been 
thinking", "can we add", "let's remove", "I changed my mind", 
"the client wants". If any of these appear, route immediately to 
@adapt.md before doing anything else.

If the user says "merge task [N]" or "merge [branch name]", 
route immediately to @merge.md.

Never assume context. Always read PROJECT.md fresh at the start of 
every session.
